{
  "texts": [
    "This presented work to show a novel integration of DEV-22 and SVM by DWT into one; in contrast, high accuracies can also be achieved at 92.3%, with significantly fewer computation requirements.",
    "While DWT indeed enhances refinement of features by hardly any added computational complexity, strong classification is ensured by the minimum overhead through SVM.",
    "Precisely, the balances of accuracy and resource efficiency made possible by PolyNetDWTCADx bring it at an optimum selection for clinical applications where real-world scalability, interpretability, and realtime performance really come at stakes.",
    "The limitation of the proposed PolynetDWTCADx framework, despite its good results in detection and segmentation tasks related to colorectal cancers, has to be put into consideration.",
    "While the CKHK-22 dataset is quite comprehensive, there is a chance that it may not completely represent global colorectal cancer case variability."
  ]
}